annotationB: Heat shock protein 83; Molecular chaperone that promotes the maturation, structural maintenance and proper regulation of specific target proteins involved for instance in cell cycle control and signal transduction. Interacts dynamically with various co-chaperones that modulate its substrate recognition, ATPase cycle and chaperone function.
